'''Nawara Ven''', known in [[Twi'leki/Legends|Ryl]] as '''Nawar'aven''' (meaning "silver-tongued") was a [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] pilot and attorney who served as a [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] pilot and Executive Officer of [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]].

==Biography==
===Joining Rogue Squadron===
Ven joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebellion]] after seeing many of his clients, whom he knew to be innocent, railroaded by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] authorities. He was invited to try and test for Rogue Squadron following its reformation.

Owing to his legal skills, Ven was often called to arbitrate disputes between squadron members. One such time was when [[Bror Jace]] was picking on [[Gavin Darklighter]], saying that to date, he was the worst pilot in the squadron. Bror Jace wanted to decide what his "punishment" should have been—namely to be "apprenticed" to the best pilot—fetching [[Caf/Legends|caf]], drafting reports, that sort of thing. However, [[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn]] argued that he was the best pilot and he wasn't particularly inclined to mess with Gavin the way that Bror wanted to. Nawara decided to argue his case before [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]], [[Tycho Celchu/Legends|Tycho Celchu]] and [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Afyon]] of the ''[[Eridain]]''. Corran agreed to add his kills to Gavin's and go by percentage averages rather than total number of kills. Unfortunately for Nawara, this meant that ''he'' was now the worst pilot in the squadron.

[[File:NawaraVen-JP.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Nawara Ven in flight uniform.]]
Nawara also began to form a relationship with [[Rhysati Ynr]] in the early days of Rogue Squadron. During the [[First Battle of Borleias|first battle]] of [[Borleias/Legends|Borleias]], Nawara was shot out of his [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] but he was rescued by [[Tycho Celchu/Legends|Tycho Celchu]] who flew a [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle/Legends|shuttle]] in the battlezone, rescuing pilots who were EVA. He participated in the [[Second Battle of Borleias]] using [[Lujayne Forge]]'s X-wing.

During the squadron's mission to infiltrate [[Coruscant/Legends|Imperial Center]], he was responsible for evaluating the inhabitants of [[Alien Protection Zone/Legends|Invisec]] to assess their support of a [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] invasion. While deep undercover with his squadmates, he successfully defended fellow Rogue Gavin Darklighter when the youth was wrongly accused of being a bigot by [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]] Rebel [[Asyr Sei'lar]].

Later, Ven led the squadron in a delegation to his home planet of [[Ryloth/Legends|Ryloth]], in order to obtain the [[ryll kor]] necessary to fight the [[Krytos virus]] ravaging Coruscant's nonhuman population.

Ven was called upon to act as defense counsel for fellow squadron member [[Tycho Celchu/Legends|Tycho Celchu]] against charges of murder and [[Treason/Legends|treason]]. The [[Trial of Tycho Celchu|trial]] ended when fellow Rogue [[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn]], whom Celchu was accused of killing, burst into the courtroom. Shortly thereafter, Ven and his squadmates resigned their commissions, in order to wage an insurgency against Isard's junta on the [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]]-producing planet [[Thyferra/Legends|Thyferra]], in the conflict that became known as the [[Bacta War]].

Ven was twice wounded when enemy [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE Fighters]] scored direct hits on his [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] fighter. While he completely recovered after the first instance, during the second a micro-[[Meteorite/Legends|meteorite]] severed his right leg below the knee. Though fitted with a prosthesis, he was no longer fit for combat. However, squad leader [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] made him Rogue Squadron's Executive Officer in recognition of his able administrative and intelligence skills.

Following the conclusion of the hunt for [[Warlord/Legends|Warlord]] [[Zsinj]], Ven retired from military service altogether and married [[Rhysati Ynr]], a woman from [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]] whom he met while with the Squadron. The two resigned their commissions to start a family. Later, he served as an officer aboard [[Booster Terrik]]'s freelance Star Destroyer ''[[Errant Venture/Legends|Errant Venture]]'' and helped to rescue [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] students stranded on [[Trogan/Legends|Trogan]] during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]].

===Legal career===
Two years after the [[Second Galactic Civil War]], Ven, working as a lawyer, [[The Galactic Federation of Free Alliances versus Luke Skywalker|defended]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] against charges brought against them by [[Chief of State (Galactic Alliance)|Chief of State]] [[Natasi Daala]] and the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]], in the Chief's attempt to bring the Jedi to heel for not adhering strictly to the law. Although he was dismayed by Skywalker's plea of guilty and the fact that he was not a part of the final agreement between Daala and his client, Ven continued to defend other [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], including [[Tahiri Veila]] and [[Valin Horn]]. While he won [[The Galactic Federation of Free Alliances versus Tahiri Veila|Veila's case]], Ven was defeated while [[The Galactic Federation of Free Alliances versus Valin Horn|defending]] Horn, successfully persuading the judge to deem the Jedi mentally unstable yet unable to prevent the man's sentence to confinement in [[Carbonite/Legends|carbonite]]. Ven later represented the entire [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]], fighting the executive order Daala had imposed on them. He won, lifting many of the restrictions.

